1
00:00:06,666 --> 00:00:08,750
[somber music playing]

2
00:00:17,125 --> 00:00:18,250
[dramatic sting]

3
00:00:19,375 --> 00:00:20,500
[dramatic sting]

4
00:00:31,583 --> 00:00:32,833
[Kujo] Are you all right?

5
00:00:36,291 --> 00:00:37,416
[girl] Yeah, why?

6
00:00:49,375 --> 00:00:51,416
I'm Mr. Kujo. I'm an attorney.

7
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,333
Please get in touch if you ever need to.

8
00:01:00,916 --> 00:01:03,708
Attorney… Kujo.

9
00:01:08,416 --> 00:01:11,541
[girl 1] Hey, hey.
Shutan's visuals are insane!

10
00:01:11,625 --> 00:01:13,625
He looks like an actual angel for real!

11
00:01:13,708 --> 00:01:15,416
Look! It's Ayame!

12
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:17,958
- [girl 1] Huh?
- No way! He's so self-obsessed!

13
00:01:18,041 --> 00:01:20,458
[girl 1] Wait, it's really him?
I'm dead! [laughs]

14
00:01:20,541 --> 00:01:22,875
Hey, smell this perfume.
I bought the same one as my bestie.

15
00:01:22,958 --> 00:01:25,458
- Oh my God, I totally love that for you!
- It's expensive.

16
00:01:25,541 --> 00:01:28,291
[girl 2] I've bought too much merch.
I'm broke.

17
00:01:28,375 --> 00:01:30,125
- I wanna quit being a fan.
- [phone chimes]

18
00:01:30,208 --> 00:01:31,458
[girl 1] I know, right?

19
00:01:31,541 --> 00:01:33,625
[girl 2] Tsukiya's perfect.
No wonder he's number one.

20
00:01:33,708 --> 00:01:35,375
MU-CHAN:
SHIZUKU, I’M ALMOST DONE WITH WORK

21
00:01:35,458 --> 00:01:37,458
[girl 1] Yes!
My account was added to the list!

22
00:01:37,541 --> 00:01:38,375
[girl 2] So jealous!

23
00:01:38,458 --> 00:01:40,958
- You edited your photo too much.
- Shut up!

24
00:01:41,458 --> 00:01:42,708
I'm going.

25
00:01:42,791 --> 00:01:43,708
[upbeat music playing]

26
00:01:43,791 --> 00:01:45,166
[girl 2] Do you know her?

27
00:01:45,666 --> 00:01:48,583
[girl 3] Shizuku Kasagi.
She's a classmate from my hometown.

28
00:01:48,666 --> 00:01:50,083
She's annoying.

29
00:01:50,166 --> 00:01:52,958
[girl 1] She wraps her wrists
in those fake bandages.

30
00:01:53,041 --> 00:01:55,250
She's always trying to get attention.
It's gross.

31
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:57,708
[phone rings]

32
00:02:01,208 --> 00:02:02,041
Mu-chan?

33
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:03,875
<i>Sorry, Shizuku.</i>

34
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:05,291
I just got some more work.

35
00:02:06,041 --> 00:02:08,791
I'll be done around the time
the first train leaves.

36
00:02:09,875 --> 00:02:11,208
I'm sorry!

37
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:13,333
[laughs]

38
00:02:13,416 --> 00:02:14,791
Hey, if you're bored,

39
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:17,291
why don't you find a hot boy online
and have fun?

40
00:02:19,333 --> 00:02:21,625
Where are all the hot guys?

41
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:28,708
[man] Hey.

42
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:29,625
[music fades]

43
00:02:30,208 --> 00:02:31,500
Your outfit's cute.

44
00:02:32,125 --> 00:02:33,125
Huh?

45
00:02:33,791 --> 00:02:35,041
I'm Shuto.

46
00:02:35,625 --> 00:02:36,583
What's your name?

47
00:02:39,875 --> 00:02:40,958
Shizuku.

48
00:02:41,791 --> 00:02:43,333
Shizuku, you say?

49
00:02:44,208 --> 00:02:45,333
That's a pretty name.

50
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:47,500
[hopeful music playing]

51
00:02:47,583 --> 00:02:50,333
[Shuto] It's dangerous to be alone
at this time of night.

52
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:52,958
Shall we have a drink?

53
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:55,916
Mm!

54
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,083
[music fades]

55
00:02:57,791 --> 00:03:00,291
You really didn't have to tag along,
you know.

56
00:03:00,375 --> 00:03:02,750
Well, I'm worried about you, Mr. Kujo.

57
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:04,166
You're worried about me?

58
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,416
[Kyogoku] Hey.

59
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:13,833
I see nothing but trouble
if you meet with that man.

60
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:16,958
No one really knows
what tomorrow will bring, do they?

61
00:03:17,041 --> 00:03:20,125
Well, it's pretty clear to me.
At least, as far as this guy is concerned.

62
00:03:20,208 --> 00:03:22,958
So, Mr. Karasuma,
allow me to apologize in advance

63
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:24,875
for any trouble I end up causing.

64
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:27,583
How about instead of apologizing now,
don't do it in the first place?

65
00:03:29,291 --> 00:03:30,166
Mmm.

66
00:03:31,208 --> 00:03:33,333
How great is this ice cream?

67
00:03:34,041 --> 00:03:35,750
Would you like some, gentlemen?

68
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:37,166
- Here.
- Oh…

69
00:03:38,041 --> 00:03:39,125
Thank you very much.

70
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:40,750
Here you go.

71
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:42,458
No. No, I'll pass.

72
00:03:43,083 --> 00:03:45,041
Don't like ice cream, huh?

73
00:03:45,125 --> 00:03:47,125
- No, it's not really that.
- [Kyogoku] Oh…

74
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:50,916
Can't bring yourself to accept
anything from a yakuza?

75
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,375
What a waste.

76
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:54,708
The ice cream's gonna melt.

77
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:59,041
So, Mr. Kyogoku, tell me.
What's on your mind?

78
00:03:59,708 --> 00:04:00,625
Huh?

79
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:01,666
[tense music playing]

80
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:05,708
Uh… I've been babysitting this CEO, uh…

81
00:04:06,208 --> 00:04:10,416
He's in charge of an adult video studio.
It's being sued, and he's in trouble.

82
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,833
Adult videos?

83
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,666
What are they being sued for?

84
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:19,333
Well, a former actress claims
she was coerced to act in adult videos.

85
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:23,208
So she wants a total halt
on the sale of her past works

86
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:25,625
and damages for whatever she went through.

87
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:30,125
A human rights lawyer,
uh, some hard ass, uh, Reiko, uh,

88
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:32,583
Kameoka is really gunning for them.

89
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:34,250
Kameoka's the lawyer?

90
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:36,166
[upbeat music playing]

91
00:04:36,250 --> 00:04:37,208
[feedback squeals]

92
00:04:37,291 --> 00:04:40,416
This country's laws go
much too easy on sexual violence.

93
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:42,958
The perpetrators remain at-large,

94
00:04:43,041 --> 00:04:46,375
free to commit sex crimes over and over
without a single consequence.

95
00:04:47,375 --> 00:04:50,166
Sexual violence is murder of the soul.

96
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:53,666
In its promotion of sexual violence,
the porn industry

97
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,416
is as evil as it gets.

98
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:58,166
Do you know her?

99
00:04:58,250 --> 00:05:01,916
Yeah. Attorney Kameoka was
my classmate in law school.

100
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,083
Huh? You were classmates?

101
00:05:05,166 --> 00:05:07,166
These women are coerced into working,

102
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:10,708
and their bodies permanently displayed
in humiliating detail.

103
00:05:10,791 --> 00:05:13,708
The women who appear in porn
are vulnerable and victimized.

104
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:18,291
We must protect their human rights
and eliminate the system of exploitation.

105
00:05:19,625 --> 00:05:21,333
The weakest need us now!

106
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:24,791
Stop sexual violence!

107
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:27,250
Shut down porn!

108
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:29,416
[crowd chanting] Stop sexual violence!
Shut down porn…

109
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:32,416
It makes me want to puke
to hear human rights lawyers go on

110
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,208
about saving the weak.

111
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:37,875
They spout ideals
so they can feel good about themselves.

112
00:05:37,958 --> 00:05:39,791
[music fades]

113
00:05:39,875 --> 00:05:41,833
Weak people just take the easiest way out.

114
00:05:41,916 --> 00:05:43,625
They don't fight. They're busy complaining

115
00:05:43,708 --> 00:05:45,291
and stabbing each other in the back.

116
00:05:45,375 --> 00:05:47,541
If your army gets weak
when you look after the wounded,

117
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:50,333
you should just kill them
and cut your losses. Otherwise,

118
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:54,583
the law of the jungle kicks in,
and a lion eats you for lunch.

119
00:05:56,375 --> 00:05:57,875
Anyway… [grunts]

120
00:05:58,541 --> 00:06:00,666
If they wanna rant about human rights,

121
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:04,625
they should look out for
the human rights of us yakuza as well.

122
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:06,458
Why would yakuza need human rights?

123
00:06:06,541 --> 00:06:07,541
[Kujo] Mr. Karasuma.

124
00:06:07,625 --> 00:06:09,916
Because yakuza are overwhelmingly strong.

125
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,708
That's just prejudiced talk.

126
00:06:12,291 --> 00:06:15,041
We can't open bank accounts.
We can't stay in hotels.

127
00:06:15,125 --> 00:06:17,791
- We don't even qualify for life insurance.
- Cry me a river.

128
00:06:17,875 --> 00:06:19,875
- [henchman] Watch your mouth.
- [Kyogoku] That'll do.

129
00:06:19,958 --> 00:06:22,916
Unlike Attorney Kujo,
his associate is still very young.

130
00:06:23,708 --> 00:06:26,583
- Cool down and eat some ice cream.
- [henchman] Thank you, sir.

131
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:30,333
Well, Attorney Kujo, I'm counting on you.

132
00:06:38,125 --> 00:06:39,208
You gonna take it?

133
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,125
- Yes.
- [wrapper rustling]

134
00:06:42,208 --> 00:06:43,791
After all, it's my job.

135
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:49,333
[theme music playing]

136
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:20,750
[man] Attorney Kameoka,
thank you very much.

137
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:24,750
I'll admit I had my doubts
about using a female attorney at first.

138
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:27,791
You're an absolute Amazon, though,
as tough and ruthless as any man would be.

139
00:07:27,875 --> 00:07:30,083
Do you understand that what you just said

140
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:33,166
is a sexist statement
arising from the discriminatory idea

141
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:34,916
that women are inferior to men?

142
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,583
Oh, no, no.

143
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:39,166
I meant it as a compliment.

144
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:43,250
You're such an attractive woman…
and a good lawyer too.

145
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:46,750
Gender and appearance have absolutely
nothing to do with an attorney's ability.

146
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:49,833
My role as a lawyer
is just to do everything I can

147
00:07:49,916 --> 00:07:51,291
to help my clients.

148
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:53,791
Mr. Suzuki, you take the subway, right?

149
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,333
Yes.

150
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:56,750
Here it is.

151
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:01,916
Uh, okay, then.

152
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:04,250
Thank you very much.

153
00:08:07,083 --> 00:08:08,625
[Nagaragi] Ms. Kameoka.

154
00:08:08,708 --> 00:08:10,291
Mr. Nagaragi.

155
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:11,208
[chuckles]

156
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:13,541
You've been doing very well
for yourself lately.

157
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:15,250
You're too kind. What's up, sir?

158
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:18,500
Oh, I was thinking
we could have a chat. Huh?

159
00:08:21,458 --> 00:08:22,875
You're single, right?

160
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:24,916
Don't you want to get married?

161
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,958
Why are you bringing this up
out of the blue?

162
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:29,291
It sounds like sexual harassment,
Mr. Nagaragi.

163
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:32,791
Is this going somewhere?

164
00:08:32,875 --> 00:08:33,833
Yes.

165
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:37,416
You gave a lecture on married couples
having different surnames.

166
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,833
I watched the video.

167
00:08:39,708 --> 00:08:41,666
I realized I have just the guy for you.

168
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,041
It's none of your concern,
but just in case, who is it?

169
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:46,250
It's Kujo, the lawyer.

170
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:47,958
Kujo the…

171
00:08:48,041 --> 00:08:49,291
[mellow music playing]

172
00:08:49,375 --> 00:08:50,750
You mean Kurama?

173
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,083
[scoffs]

174
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:54,166
Surely you can't be serious
about that weirdo.

175
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:55,125
[chuckles]

176
00:08:55,208 --> 00:08:58,291
His clients are major criminals.
His reputation is terrible.

177
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:03,291
Are you saying
that I would be a good match

178
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:05,250
for someone who works
for a bunch of gangsters?

179
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:06,583
Yeah.

180
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:10,333
I can totally picture
the two of you as a couple.

181
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:11,916
That's insulting.

182
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,791
He's a man of principle, actually.

183
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:15,416
This is ridiculous.

184
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,333
Well, I'm off.

185
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:19,250
Meet him once

186
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:22,291
and rekindle an old friendship?

187
00:09:23,916 --> 00:09:25,000
Excuse me.

188
00:09:38,375 --> 00:09:39,833
- [chuckles]
- [music ends]

189
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:44,041
Kasagi!
How many times do I have to tell you?

190
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:46,583
You have to stock the product
with the right price tag.

191
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:49,458
I'm sorry.

192
00:09:51,083 --> 00:09:55,833
Oh, man…
No matter what I do, I suck at it.

193
00:09:57,250 --> 00:09:58,666
- [phone chimes]
- [sighs]

194
00:10:02,958 --> 00:10:04,416
It's Shuto!

195
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,583
[Shuto] <i>Are you feeling down?</i>

196
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:08,375
<i>Come to the bar.</i>

197
00:10:08,458 --> 00:10:09,958
<i>I'll cheer you up.</i>

198
00:10:11,291 --> 00:10:15,250
Shuto, I'd love for you to cheer me up
more than anything.

199
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,833
<i>But I'm all out of savings.</i>

200
00:10:19,916 --> 00:10:21,541
<i>I'm in my broke era.</i>

201
00:10:22,208 --> 00:10:24,166
<i>I can't come to the bar.</i>

202
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:25,875
<i>Sob.</i>

203
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:30,416
[phone beeps]

204
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,833
[Shuto] <i>You can pay later. Just come.</i>

205
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:38,458
<i>I wanna see you, Shizuku.</i>

206
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:42,625
[chuckles]

207
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:44,625
- [dance music playing in background]
- [gulping]

208
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:46,166
[sighs]

209
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:48,208
[chuckles drunkenly]

210
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:52,333
I had… so much fun today.

211
00:10:52,416 --> 00:10:54,583
Thank you for coming
to hang out with me, Shizuku.

212
00:10:54,666 --> 00:10:57,791
- Shuto, I can't get over how cool you are.
- [Shuto] Hm?

213
00:10:57,875 --> 00:10:59,833
I was sure you were a pimp when we met.

214
00:10:59,916 --> 00:11:01,958
I'm not a pimp. I told you.

215
00:11:02,458 --> 00:11:04,041
I'm an actor, mostly.

216
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:06,625
- I work just part-time here.
- [chuckles]

217
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:09,041
Right, you're an actor.

218
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:10,333
What were you in again?

219
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:12,666
Well, there's a superhero show
that's really cool.

220
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,375
I came close to getting a role.

221
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:18,083
You're gonna be such a great actor.
I'm sure of it.

222
00:11:19,166 --> 00:11:20,625
I'm just getting started.

223
00:11:21,666 --> 00:11:23,541
What's your dream, Shizuku?

224
00:11:25,208 --> 00:11:26,708
Uh, my dream?

225
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:30,541
I'm just doing whatever to get by.

226
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:34,625
All I really want is to leave home,
move out as soon as I can.

227
00:11:34,708 --> 00:11:37,000
I'm trying to save a little bit of money.

228
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:39,208
Are you fighting with your parents?

229
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:42,458
[Shizuku] It's not my parents.

230
00:11:42,541 --> 00:11:43,458
[ominous music playing]

231
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:47,208
[Shizuku] <i>It's my mom's boyfriend,</i>
<i>Tonohata. I hate him.</i>

232
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:49,666
- [Ms. Kasagi] Tono, honey?
- [Tonohata] What?

233
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,791
[Ms. Kasagi] Get yourself
something to eat with this.

234
00:11:51,875 --> 00:11:52,916
[Tonohata] Got it.

235
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,833
[Ms. Kasagi sighs] Shizuku,
I'm going to work.

236
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:57,750
[Shizuku] Yeah. See you.

237
00:11:58,458 --> 00:11:59,541
[door closes]

238
00:11:59,625 --> 00:12:00,791
[footsteps approaching]

239
00:12:00,875 --> 00:12:04,875
[Shizuku] <i>He does nasty things to me</i>
<i>when my mom's not around.</i>

240
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:10,416
He hits me if I try to resist,
so I'm really scared.

241
00:12:14,708 --> 00:12:18,166
I always go on about my problems
when I get drunk.

242
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:21,000
I'm sorry. I hope you don't hate me.

243
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:24,250
There's no way
I could hate you for that, Shizuku.

244
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,916
Every day you hang out with me.

245
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:30,916
When you're here,
you spend a lot of money.

246
00:12:31,583 --> 00:12:32,750
I just wanna thank you.

247
00:12:33,875 --> 00:12:35,291
I'm happy.

248
00:12:37,125 --> 00:12:41,083
But my… my money's going to run out soon.

249
00:12:42,458 --> 00:12:44,791
My tab is basically maxed out.

250
00:12:46,958 --> 00:12:47,791
[Shuto] Shizuku,

251
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:53,333
let's be alone together…
after I close tonight.

252
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,291
[music builds]

253
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:06,958
Shuto, I feel so safe
whenever I'm with you.

254
00:13:10,208 --> 00:13:12,958
I've never felt this safe before.

255
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:15,500
For real?

256
00:13:16,416 --> 00:13:17,625
I'm so glad.

257
00:13:19,583 --> 00:13:20,708
Yeah.

258
00:13:23,125 --> 00:13:25,541
Shizuku, there's a job
I wanna hook you up with.

259
00:13:25,625 --> 00:13:26,791
[music fades]

260
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:31,291
Oh, okay.

261
00:13:31,875 --> 00:13:34,083
It's a sex thing, right?

262
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:45,750
Shuto, I'll do whatever you say
as long as I can keep seeing you.

263
00:13:47,541 --> 00:13:52,250
The other girls I know are working
as escorts for their pimp boyfriends too.

264
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:53,250
Not that.

265
00:13:54,791 --> 00:13:57,000
Shizuku, don't underestimate yourself.

266
00:13:58,416 --> 00:13:59,250
Huh?

267
00:14:00,666 --> 00:14:01,666
RECORDING

268
00:14:01,750 --> 00:14:03,208
[man] And action.

269
00:14:04,166 --> 00:14:05,083
[Shizuku] Okay.

270
00:14:07,083 --> 00:14:09,583
A scout named Shuto
said I should come here.

271
00:14:09,666 --> 00:14:11,250
My name is Shizuku Kasagi.

272
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:14,750
Your acquaintances are going
to find out for sure.

273
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:16,041
You're okay with that?

274
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:18,125
Yes, I'm okay with it.

275
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:21,208
It doesn't matter.
I don't have anyone I'm worried about.

276
00:14:22,041 --> 00:14:22,916
But

277
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:27,125
can a girl like me really become one?

278
00:14:27,208 --> 00:14:30,208
Ms. Kasagi,
you shouldn't sell yourself short.

279
00:14:31,125 --> 00:14:34,125
I think you've got the talent
to be an A-list actress.

280
00:14:34,708 --> 00:14:35,875
An A-list actress?

281
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:39,958
Only a few of the most elite actresses
get to the A-list.

282
00:14:40,541 --> 00:14:42,416
Have confidence in yourself.

283
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,458
Yes, sir.

284
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:47,291
I'm gonna try to be more confident.
Confidence is what I need.

285
00:14:47,375 --> 00:14:48,333
You'll be fine.

286
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:52,208
Once you see how easy it is,
you'll get all the confidence you need.

287
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,000
You are

288
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:56,541
a diamond in the rough.

289
00:14:57,041 --> 00:14:59,041
[mellow music playing]

290
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,666
[brushing teeth]

291
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:17,500
You're so pretty, Shizuku.

292
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:20,166
They know how to film you just right.
You'll look beautiful.

293
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:23,750
Ms. Tashiro, thank you. Thank you so much.

294
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:24,833
[Ms. Tashiro] Hm.

295
00:15:27,041 --> 00:15:28,000
But I'm…

296
00:15:30,041 --> 00:15:31,125
scared.

297
00:15:32,416 --> 00:15:34,375
[Ms. Tashiro] Don't worry, sweetheart.

298
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:37,375
I'll be right there
watching over you the whole time.

299
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:38,750
So relax.

300
00:15:39,416 --> 00:15:41,458
- Thank you, Ms. Tashiro.
- [Ms. Tashiro] Okay.

301
00:15:45,458 --> 00:15:46,500
You're all set.

302
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:00,541
[phone chimes]

303
00:16:05,416 --> 00:16:06,416
[Shuto] <i>Shizuku.</i>

304
00:16:06,916 --> 00:16:08,583
<i>Good luck with the shoot.</i>

305
00:16:09,166 --> 00:16:11,083
<i>I'll always be right there with you.</i>

306
00:16:16,083 --> 00:16:18,083
[music increases in tempo]

307
00:16:31,083 --> 00:16:33,291
Hello, everyone. Nice to meet you.

308
00:16:33,375 --> 00:16:34,250
[music fades]

309
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:35,208
Nice to meet you.

310
00:16:35,708 --> 00:16:39,000
My name is Koyama.
I was referred to you by Mr. Kyogoku.

311
00:16:39,875 --> 00:16:41,750
How do you do? I'm Attorney Kujo.

312
00:16:42,666 --> 00:16:43,541
I'm Karasuma.

313
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:45,708
I'm here about the lawsuit.

314
00:16:45,791 --> 00:16:50,083
Momoka Shiraishi claims her performances
were coerced and wants the titles pulled.

315
00:16:51,041 --> 00:16:54,750
Well, to put it bluntly,
you don't have much of a case, sir.

316
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:55,666
Really?

317
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,541
- [Kujo] 'Fraid so.
- Why is that?

318
00:16:57,625 --> 00:17:00,416
Although this was before
the new law on adult videos took effect,

319
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,833
considering the legal precedents,

320
00:17:01,916 --> 00:17:05,208
we think it's highly likely
that Ms. Shiraishi's work in the videos

321
00:17:05,291 --> 00:17:08,541
will be seen as falling under
a quasi-employment contract.

322
00:17:09,375 --> 00:17:12,500
In this case,
the provisions on employment and labor

323
00:17:12,583 --> 00:17:13,916
under the Civil Code shall apply,

324
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,958
so she can always quit
in the middle of a contract.

325
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:16,958
She can't be forced.

326
00:17:17,041 --> 00:17:20,208
Regarding her demands for damages
and for her films to be removed,

327
00:17:20,291 --> 00:17:23,625
unless you have concrete evidence
that she wasn't coerced into performing,

328
00:17:23,708 --> 00:17:26,750
in our view, you've almost no chance
of winning this case.

329
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:29,125
The other party's lawyer will make
a big deal in the media.

330
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:32,541
- That's something we have to look out for.
- What a drag.

331
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:35,625
After they brought in the new law,
we all cleaned up our act.

332
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:37,291
Not like the old days.

333
00:17:37,375 --> 00:17:41,208
Now, we make damn sure we sign contracts
with actresses before we shoot.

334
00:17:41,291 --> 00:17:43,625
You mean you didn't sign contracts
in the past?

335
00:17:43,708 --> 00:17:44,708
Huh?

336
00:17:48,916 --> 00:17:51,041
Oh, well…

337
00:17:52,583 --> 00:17:54,958
The actress who's suing us,
Momoka Shiraishi,

338
00:17:55,041 --> 00:17:57,125
has been working with us for ages.

339
00:18:00,541 --> 00:18:03,250
She's appeared in upwards of 300 titles.

340
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:06,958
Then she wakes up one day and says
she was forced to perform in them.

341
00:18:07,041 --> 00:18:09,375
The fact that she's appeared
in more than 300 videos

342
00:18:09,458 --> 00:18:12,166
may indicate that
she was not forced to appear in them.

343
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:16,458
Have you thought about why
she decided to file the lawsuit now?

344
00:18:16,541 --> 00:18:18,250
Because of a guy. A guy.

345
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:19,166
[Shiraishi panting]

346
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:22,250
[Koyama] <i>Shiraishi had a boyfriend</i>
<i>who liked to hit her.</i>

347
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:26,000
<i>At first, she put up with the beatings</i>
<i>and let him steal her money.</i>

348
00:18:26,750 --> 00:18:29,791
<i>But after a while,</i>
<i>she couldn't take the violence anymore.</i>

349
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:34,333
<i>So she went off to Reiko Kameoka,</i>
<i>a human rights lawyer.</i>

350
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:36,750
God knows why she focused her anger on us

351
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:38,416
instead of the abusive boyfriend.

352
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:41,416
What was the relationship like
between your studio and Ms. Shiraishi?

353
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,833
It was all good.

354
00:18:42,916 --> 00:18:45,666
She even sent me a postcard
from her trip abroad.

355
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:46,750
[bag zipping]

356
00:18:48,541 --> 00:18:49,500
Have a look.

357
00:18:52,291 --> 00:18:54,625
ALOHA, PRESIDENT! I’LL DO MY BEST
AFTER I REST UP!! MOMOKA

358
00:18:54,708 --> 00:18:57,458
[Koyama] It's ridiculous.
They keep coming up with all these claims.

359
00:18:57,541 --> 00:18:59,416
What kind of human rights lawyer is she?

360
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:01,958
Does she think
that we don't have any human rights?

361
00:19:02,625 --> 00:19:06,291
But anyway… I'm counting on you, sir.

362
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:08,708
I agree to take the case.

363
00:19:08,791 --> 00:19:13,416
However, whether she keeps working in porn
is entirely up to Ms. Shiraishi to decide.

364
00:19:17,958 --> 00:19:19,833
[music fades]

365
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:20,875
[sighs]

366
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:32,000
[Karasuma] You're regretting it,
aren't you?

367
00:19:33,083 --> 00:19:33,916
Regretting what?

368
00:19:35,166 --> 00:19:37,416
Getting involved in a case like this one.

369
00:19:38,541 --> 00:19:40,541
You should stay away from Mr. Kyogoku.

370
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:44,416
No. I was thinking about something else.

371
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:46,583
What were you thinking about?

372
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:50,625
Isn't every kind of lawyer
basically a human rights lawyer?

373
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:51,583
Huh?

374
00:19:51,666 --> 00:19:54,666
Lawyers have clients who need help,
so they get down to work.

375
00:19:55,166 --> 00:19:56,458
When they fight in court,

376
00:19:56,541 --> 00:19:58,875
they stand up
for their client's basic rights.

377
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:02,541
Wouldn't you say it makes all lawyers,
including you and me,

378
00:20:02,625 --> 00:20:03,958
defenders of human rights?

379
00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:05,083
- Actually…
- [phone buzzes]

380
00:20:05,166 --> 00:20:07,166
…a human rights lawyer is someone who…

381
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:10,708
Kameoka's calling us.

382
00:20:10,791 --> 00:20:11,791
<i>Hello?</i>

383
00:20:12,541 --> 00:20:14,541
It's been a while. It's Kameoka here.

384
00:20:15,041 --> 00:20:17,833
Kurama… No, that's not it.
You're Kujo now, right?

385
00:20:18,916 --> 00:20:21,541
<i>Your last name changed,</i>
<i>but you still have the same phone number</i>

386
00:20:21,625 --> 00:20:23,166
<i>from your student days.</i>

387
00:20:24,041 --> 00:20:26,041
Ms. Kameoka, it's been a while.

388
00:20:27,041 --> 00:20:27,875
[phone clattering]

389
00:20:28,458 --> 00:20:31,833
Mr. Kujo,
you're representing Komuora Kikaku, right?

390
00:20:32,666 --> 00:20:34,625
Can I ask you a question
before we get into this?

391
00:20:36,041 --> 00:20:37,166
Sure.

392
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,125
[Kameoka] <i>You have a daughter, don't you?</i>

393
00:20:40,375 --> 00:20:43,208
<i>What would you do</i>
<i>if your daughter were forced into porn?</i>

394
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:46,875
As far as the case is concerned,
Ms. Kameoka,

395
00:20:47,375 --> 00:20:51,583
how can an actress be forced to do porn
if she's acted in 300 videos?

396
00:20:51,666 --> 00:20:53,833
Don't answer a question with a question.

397
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:56,291
[Kujo] <i>This isn't a problem</i>
<i>with the porn industry.</i>

398
00:20:56,375 --> 00:21:00,041
In fact, your client is blaming her job
when the real issue is domestic violence.

399
00:21:00,625 --> 00:21:03,541
Your daughter. Answer my question, okay?

400
00:21:03,625 --> 00:21:07,333
Just imagine somebody made her do porn.
What do you think you would do?

401
00:21:07,416 --> 00:21:08,875
That's a huge leap.

402
00:21:09,375 --> 00:21:10,791
It has nothing to do with this case.

403
00:21:12,583 --> 00:21:13,708
[sighs]

404
00:21:14,666 --> 00:21:16,125
So I'll change my question.

405
00:21:18,166 --> 00:21:20,750
Why are you always defending
scumbags and gangsters?

406
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:21,833
[tense music playing]

407
00:21:21,916 --> 00:21:25,583
<i>It's one thing to fight for social justice</i>
<i>and defend the wrongly accused.</i>

408
00:21:25,666 --> 00:21:29,666
But… whenever your clients walk,
you're just encouraging crime.

409
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:32,958
The way I see things,

410
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:36,000
it's never a good idea for a lawyer
to make a judgment about justice.

411
00:21:36,083 --> 00:21:39,333
You're a human being
before you're a lawyer, right?

412
00:21:40,125 --> 00:21:42,291
If you can't decide
what's good and evil on your own,

413
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:43,708
you're not a real human being.

414
00:21:48,458 --> 00:21:53,333
When the powers you serve are evil,
eventually that evil will swallow you.

415
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:56,333
[tense percussive music playing]

416
00:22:03,208 --> 00:22:06,333
[Karasuma] <i>Isn't she the epitome</i>
<i>of a human rights lawyer?</i>

417
00:22:06,416 --> 00:22:08,250
Is that what you think?

418
00:22:08,916 --> 00:22:11,541
I wouldn't describe her
as a lawyer exactly.

419
00:22:12,083 --> 00:22:14,083
She strikes me more
as a thinker or activist

420
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:16,000
with a strong desire for approval.

421
00:22:16,083 --> 00:22:19,875
[Karasuma] Well, at the very least,
she's not one of those corrupt lawyers.

422
00:22:20,458 --> 00:22:23,458
I imagine the two of you
would get along very well.

423
00:22:23,541 --> 00:22:26,916
I bet the moment she lays eyes on me,
she'll cut me down to size.

424
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,500
The last thing she said to you
was spot on, though.

425
00:22:30,583 --> 00:22:31,583
Mr. Kujo.

426
00:22:33,416 --> 00:22:35,750
I urge you to be very careful

427
00:22:36,458 --> 00:22:39,291
with anything Mr. Kyogoku asks of you.

428
00:22:44,375 --> 00:22:45,583
I'll bear that in mind.

429
00:22:48,583 --> 00:22:49,500
[music fades]

430
00:22:50,833 --> 00:22:51,875
[man] Jackpot! It's a hit!

431
00:22:51,958 --> 00:22:54,125
ADULT VIDEO DEBUT
DIAMOND IN THE ROUGH, NOW AVAILABLE

432
00:22:54,250 --> 00:22:56,250
It's true we spent a ton on advertising,

433
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:59,250
but look at how this thing is selling.
Shizuku, wow!

434
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:01,875
Thank you, President Ao! Thank you!

435
00:23:01,958 --> 00:23:03,625
At the shoot tomorrow,
I'll do my very best!

436
00:23:03,708 --> 00:23:05,875
- [Ao] Oh, all right!
- [Shizuku and Shuto] Cheers!

437
00:23:05,958 --> 00:23:07,916
[indistinct chatter]

438
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,958
[dance music playing in background]

439
00:23:10,041 --> 00:23:11,625
It's delicious.

440
00:23:11,708 --> 00:23:13,250
Are you sure? This costs a lot.

441
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:15,041
Sure, it's to celebrate your debut.

442
00:23:15,125 --> 00:23:18,041
And you're first in the rankings already,
right? You go, girl!

443
00:23:18,125 --> 00:23:22,250
Oh! I got paid,
so I can settle the tab that I owe you.

444
00:23:22,333 --> 00:23:25,958
Oh, it's okay. Soon, you'll be famous.
So, you can just pay me then.

445
00:23:26,958 --> 00:23:27,875
Mm!

446
00:23:28,500 --> 00:23:29,500
[Shuto] More importantly,

447
00:23:29,583 --> 00:23:32,416
the actor who got the role
in that morning show wants to meet you.

448
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:35,875
Nah. As long as I have you,
Shuto, no one else counts.

449
00:23:37,500 --> 00:23:38,625
Is that right?

450
00:23:38,708 --> 00:23:39,625
[Shizuku] Yeah.

451
00:23:41,666 --> 00:23:44,333
Ah, I'm so happy.

452
00:23:45,125 --> 00:23:46,333
Hey, Shizuku.

453
00:23:46,916 --> 00:23:48,750
Can you stay till the bar closes?

454
00:23:49,375 --> 00:23:50,208
Yeah.

455
00:23:50,291 --> 00:23:52,083
You'll be in my arms all night.

456
00:23:52,166 --> 00:23:53,875
- Yay!
- [both chuckle]

457
00:23:55,750 --> 00:23:57,083
- [chuckles]
- [phone chimes]

458
00:23:57,708 --> 00:23:58,541
Oh!

459
00:23:59,166 --> 00:24:01,666
MOM:
SHIZUKU, THE MONEY’S DUE TODAY

460
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:03,333
COME HOME

461
00:24:03,416 --> 00:24:05,208
WHERE ARE YOU?

462
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:08,583
What is it?

463
00:24:09,375 --> 00:24:10,666
I'm sorry.

464
00:24:12,041 --> 00:24:14,083
My mom's getting all worked up.

465
00:24:14,166 --> 00:24:15,458
- [laughing]
- [jazzy music playing]

466
00:24:15,541 --> 00:24:17,708
[Tonohata] You're such a pain in the ass,
you know that?

467
00:24:17,791 --> 00:24:20,583
Ow, ow, ow! That hurts, Tono! It hurts!

468
00:24:20,666 --> 00:24:21,750
I told you.

469
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:24,708
You have to use your brain
if you wanna make money, dude!

470
00:24:24,791 --> 00:24:26,083
Check out this bad boy.

471
00:24:27,958 --> 00:24:30,458
Phony, sure,
but it's almost the real thing.

472
00:24:30,958 --> 00:24:32,125
Comes from Korea.

473
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:37,000
I made the rounds of some pawn shops
and got an easy 500,000.

474
00:24:37,083 --> 00:24:37,916
No shit?

475
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,875
- They fell for it just like that?
- Ha.

476
00:24:39,958 --> 00:24:41,583
I just said, "How would I know?"

477
00:24:41,666 --> 00:24:43,958
"You could've switched it out."
So then they had to buy it.

478
00:24:44,041 --> 00:24:45,958
[both laugh]

479
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:49,208
For you, a special deal. You give me 250k.

480
00:24:49,958 --> 00:24:52,166
You unload it as the real thing
at an auction online.

481
00:24:52,250 --> 00:24:54,000
Nah, I haven't got that kind of cash.

482
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:57,625
But hey, you said you'd pay me
the 100k you owe me today, right?

483
00:25:00,708 --> 00:25:01,875
Watch this move.

484
00:25:02,375 --> 00:25:03,291
[man] Huh?

485
00:25:06,291 --> 00:25:08,500
- [growling]
- [groans]

486
00:25:08,583 --> 00:25:11,500
Your broke ass is getting on my nerves!
Take the damn watch.

487
00:25:11,583 --> 00:25:13,916
- Sell it for 500 grand. You'll make 250!
- Hey, guys, come on.

488
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:15,416
You're gonna break the glasses.

489
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:18,333
- [Tonohata] You got a problem with that?
- [man] Get off me.

490
00:25:18,416 --> 00:25:20,833
- [Tonohata] I can't hear you! Which is it?
- Oh, Shizuku.

491
00:25:20,916 --> 00:25:23,208
- [music ends]
- [Tonohata] Hey, Shizuku!

492
00:25:23,291 --> 00:25:26,458
Where the hell did you get to?
I've been worried about you.

493
00:25:26,541 --> 00:25:28,083
I was just working.

494
00:25:29,833 --> 00:25:32,208
Looks like you're filling out.
You got a boyfriend?

495
00:25:32,291 --> 00:25:33,208
Of course not!

496
00:25:33,708 --> 00:25:34,541
Mama.

497
00:25:36,291 --> 00:25:37,291
Yeah?

498
00:25:38,666 --> 00:25:40,250
Here's the money.

499
00:25:40,333 --> 00:25:41,250
Oh.

500
00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:44,125
What?

501
00:25:44,625 --> 00:25:47,250
All this? Wait, where's this money from?

502
00:25:47,333 --> 00:25:48,500
My job.

503
00:25:48,583 --> 00:25:50,791
Oh, really? [chuckles]

504
00:25:50,875 --> 00:25:53,708
Well, Um… I'm gonna go now.

505
00:25:53,791 --> 00:25:54,875
Uh-huh.

506
00:25:55,916 --> 00:25:57,916
[indistinct chatter]

507
00:26:01,666 --> 00:26:02,541
Hey.

508
00:26:03,250 --> 00:26:04,500
Hand over the cash.

509
00:26:04,583 --> 00:26:05,791
No, you're not getting it.

510
00:26:05,875 --> 00:26:08,250
Do you have any idea
how much your tab is these days, Tono?

511
00:26:08,333 --> 00:26:10,250
And it's me who's gonna get shit
from the owner.

512
00:26:10,333 --> 00:26:12,166
Shut your trap. Just cover it for me!

513
00:26:12,250 --> 00:26:15,083
Tono, it's about time
you go get yourself a job.

514
00:26:17,958 --> 00:26:20,375
Quit acting all high and mighty!

515
00:26:20,958 --> 00:26:23,833
You landed us a real honey,
you know. Thanks a lot!

516
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:25,833
[Shuto] <i>I have to admit, I had no idea</i>

517
00:26:25,916 --> 00:26:28,000
Shizuku would blow up like that either.

518
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:30,666
[Ao] <i>And she still has a lot of potential.</i>

519
00:26:32,041 --> 00:26:35,333
An actress has to be strong
to survive in this business.

520
00:26:35,416 --> 00:26:37,375
If she's weak, she'll flame out.

521
00:26:37,875 --> 00:26:41,000
She'd better get a thick skin and learn
to forget about the little things.

522
00:26:41,833 --> 00:26:45,458
<i>And when it comes to the crazy girls,</i>
<i>we have to pour on the smooth talk.</i>

523
00:26:45,541 --> 00:26:47,791
<i>If it turns out Shizuku's the crazy type,</i>

524
00:26:47,875 --> 00:26:50,458
<i>I'm counting on you</i>
<i>to keep her from flipping out.</i>

525
00:26:51,250 --> 00:26:53,125
Yeah. I got this, as usual.

526
00:26:54,041 --> 00:26:57,000
Oh. There's another girl behind
on her bar tab,

527
00:26:57,083 --> 00:26:59,333
<i>so I think I can introduce you to her</i>
<i>pretty soon.</i>

528
00:26:59,416 --> 00:27:01,375
[Ao] Nice. You're a hard worker.

529
00:27:01,458 --> 00:27:03,541
[Shuto] <i>Well, if the girl I send over</i>
<i>makes money,</i>

530
00:27:03,625 --> 00:27:06,791
<i>I get my 10% scouting fee</i>
<i>for the length of her career.</i>

531
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:08,958
- [unsettling music playing]
- It's a good line of work.

532
00:27:09,041 --> 00:27:10,166
[door opens]

533
00:27:10,250 --> 00:27:12,458
- Something's up. I'll call you later.
- [door closes]

534
00:27:13,375 --> 00:27:14,291
[Shuto] Shizuku?

535
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:15,833
[exhales]

536
00:27:15,916 --> 00:27:16,750
What's wrong?

537
00:27:16,833 --> 00:27:18,208
I'm through with this.

538
00:27:19,500 --> 00:27:21,666
I don't ever want to go home.

539
00:27:22,458 --> 00:27:24,791
I wanna be next to you forever.

540
00:27:31,875 --> 00:27:32,791
Okay.

541
00:27:34,791 --> 00:27:36,000
[man] Huh?

542
00:27:36,083 --> 00:27:37,625
Postpone the interview?

543
00:27:37,708 --> 00:27:38,541
[Kameoka] <i>Yes.</i>

544
00:27:38,625 --> 00:27:40,333
My client, Ms. Momoka Shiraishi,

545
00:27:40,416 --> 00:27:42,375
has settled out of court
and withdrawn the lawsuit.

546
00:27:42,458 --> 00:27:43,416
Ah, man.

547
00:27:43,916 --> 00:27:46,916
So… what about the exposé
I was writing on porn?

548
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:48,208
Huh? Okay.

549
00:27:48,291 --> 00:27:49,541
You're out of luck.

550
00:27:50,416 --> 00:27:51,458
They got us.

551
00:27:52,333 --> 00:27:55,458
The lawyer for the other side
suggested a deal, and she caved.

552
00:27:56,208 --> 00:27:57,416
Attorney Kujo.

553
00:27:57,500 --> 00:28:01,208
I wanna thank you for getting us
a settlement on the Shiraishi case.

554
00:28:01,291 --> 00:28:02,208
No problem.

555
00:28:04,375 --> 00:28:05,666
It was just like you said.

556
00:28:05,750 --> 00:28:08,250
Ms. Kameoka was just
using Momoka Shiraishi

557
00:28:08,333 --> 00:28:10,791
as the public face
of her campaign against the business.

558
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:14,125
The only thing I did was
supply an explanation.

559
00:28:15,166 --> 00:28:17,083
I'd say it was pretty effective.

560
00:28:17,708 --> 00:28:20,708
Have we established why Momoka Shiraishi
sued in the first place?

561
00:28:20,791 --> 00:28:21,791
Uh…

562
00:28:22,666 --> 00:28:25,583
It was after her boyfriend gave her
a serious beating. She was confused.

563
00:28:25,666 --> 00:28:27,833
Kameoka got her hooks into her,
and she felt cornered.

564
00:28:27,916 --> 00:28:29,041
She said it was a mistake.

565
00:28:29,625 --> 00:28:31,333
What's going to happen to her now?

566
00:28:31,416 --> 00:28:35,708
Well, she turned against the industry,
so she won't be welcomed back.

567
00:28:36,208 --> 00:28:39,250
She could have been able
to make a comeback otherwise.

568
00:28:42,166 --> 00:28:45,250
<i>The girls who made it big once</i>
<i>always come back again.</i>

569
00:28:45,333 --> 00:28:47,416
<i>No one will hire them</i>
<i>for a respectable job.</i>

570
00:28:48,416 --> 00:28:50,791
<i>And when they're done,</i>
<i>they start to miss the time</i>

571
00:28:50,875 --> 00:28:52,791
<i>when they had somewhere they belonged.</i>

572
00:28:54,958 --> 00:28:55,875
[music fades]

573
00:28:55,958 --> 00:28:57,250
[indistinct chatter]

574
00:28:57,333 --> 00:28:58,583
Here's your sweet and sour pork.

575
00:28:58,666 --> 00:28:59,916
- [Karasuma] Mm!
- Oh, thank you.

576
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,250
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

577
00:29:01,333 --> 00:29:04,291
It's pretty unusual
you inviting us out for a meal.

578
00:29:04,375 --> 00:29:06,041
You even invited Mr. Kujo.

579
00:29:06,791 --> 00:29:09,666
Every now and then,
I have to warn these crooked lawyers

580
00:29:09,750 --> 00:29:10,916
about the error of their ways.

581
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,125
Crooked lawyers?

582
00:29:12,208 --> 00:29:15,125
It's like a fire drill
but for crime prevention, yeah?

583
00:29:15,625 --> 00:29:17,791
Sorry for always making you worry
about us.

584
00:29:18,375 --> 00:29:19,333
And now,

585
00:29:19,916 --> 00:29:21,166
I have something to ask you two.

586
00:29:21,250 --> 00:29:23,083
The rate is 5,000 for 30 minutes,
excluding tax.

587
00:29:23,166 --> 00:29:24,708
No, it's not a legal consultation.

588
00:29:24,791 --> 00:29:25,791
[Kujo] Oh, okay.

589
00:29:27,375 --> 00:29:28,208
Here.

590
00:29:31,708 --> 00:29:32,833
It's a dating app.

591
00:29:33,708 --> 00:29:36,916
So I registered, right?
How come I don't get any responses?

592
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,291
Well, you put quite a few conditions.
Look.

593
00:29:39,375 --> 00:29:40,500
[upbeat music playing]

594
00:29:40,583 --> 00:29:42,125
Someone who is good at parallel parking.

595
00:29:42,208 --> 00:29:43,916
Someone who usually eats
three bowls of rice.

596
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:46,041
Someone who can score over 200 in bowling?

597
00:29:46,125 --> 00:29:49,375
Well, I thought
I should specify what I like in detail.

598
00:29:49,458 --> 00:29:50,416
[Karasuma] Too much.

599
00:29:50,500 --> 00:29:52,916
Oh, what's this?
"Dogs, cats, and birds are okay."

600
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:54,166
"Reptiles are not okay."

601
00:29:54,250 --> 00:29:55,166
Pets, right?

602
00:29:55,250 --> 00:29:59,041
I want someone who likes dogs, cats,
and birds as pets, but not reptiles.

603
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,291
Expecting to find someone who meets
all these conditions

604
00:30:02,375 --> 00:30:03,583
is like looking for a chimera.

605
00:30:04,250 --> 00:30:05,875
What's a chimera?

606
00:30:05,958 --> 00:30:08,458
Wait. This is weird.
Mr. Kujo fits the bill.

607
00:30:08,541 --> 00:30:11,208
You live with Black Thunder,
and you're pretty good at bowling, right?

608
00:30:11,291 --> 00:30:13,375
Sure. I once scored 292.

609
00:30:15,125 --> 00:30:16,041
What do you say?

610
00:30:16,125 --> 00:30:18,708
No way. I'm not interested
in a shady lawyer like him!

611
00:30:18,791 --> 00:30:21,750
- You don't like him because he's shady?
- [Yakushimae] No, that's not even it.

612
00:30:21,833 --> 00:30:22,833
Well,

613
00:30:23,375 --> 00:30:24,416
what about Mr. Karasuma?

614
00:30:26,666 --> 00:30:30,500
A shady lawyer's bad enough.
The helper to a shady lawyer's even worse.

615
00:30:32,125 --> 00:30:33,125
[music fades]

616
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:37,500
Whoo! Let's go to another place,
Mr. Karasuma.

617
00:30:37,583 --> 00:30:39,291
[Karasuma] You don't like me, do you?

618
00:30:39,375 --> 00:30:42,125
[laughs] Listen to you still sulking.

619
00:30:42,208 --> 00:30:43,166
You're coming, right?

620
00:30:43,250 --> 00:30:44,583
Don't be a bore like Kujo

621
00:30:44,666 --> 00:30:47,166
and decide you've got to have
an early night, okay?

622
00:30:48,750 --> 00:30:49,958
[Kyogoku] Attorney!

623
00:30:53,541 --> 00:30:54,750
You know him?

624
00:30:54,833 --> 00:30:55,666
Huh?

625
00:30:56,166 --> 00:30:57,000
Uh…

626
00:30:57,083 --> 00:30:59,666
Thank you for getting
that settlement for us. Koyama.

627
00:30:59,750 --> 00:31:02,000
The president expressed
his appreciation too.

628
00:31:02,083 --> 00:31:05,500
But how did you guys change the mind
of that, uh, porn actress?

629
00:31:06,083 --> 00:31:07,041
Porn actress?

630
00:31:07,541 --> 00:31:10,791
Actually, Attorney Kujo was in charge
of all the work.

631
00:31:10,875 --> 00:31:12,541
[Kyogoku] But, uh,

632
00:31:12,625 --> 00:31:13,875
you worked alongside him.

633
00:31:13,958 --> 00:31:15,666
You gave him some help too, right?

634
00:31:18,458 --> 00:31:21,250
Next time I see you,
the ice cream's on me.

635
00:31:21,333 --> 00:31:22,583
The least I can do.

636
00:31:23,708 --> 00:31:25,708
[tense music playing]

637
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:32,416
He's evil,
and you're an accomplice. I knew it.

638
00:31:32,500 --> 00:31:33,416
No, I'm not.

639
00:31:34,333 --> 00:31:35,500
Deny it all you want.

640
00:31:35,583 --> 00:31:38,000
If you're working with him,
that's what you are.

641
00:31:40,208 --> 00:31:41,333
That's a buzzkill.

642
00:31:42,583 --> 00:31:43,583
I'm going home.

643
00:31:53,541 --> 00:31:55,958
I'm really worried about you, you know.

644
00:31:58,208 --> 00:32:01,333
I'm worried about Mr. Kujo,
and I'm worried about you.

645
00:32:01,416 --> 00:32:03,750
[upbeat music playing]

646
00:32:11,750 --> 00:32:13,291
- [music ends]
- [Kujo] Go get it.

647
00:32:16,958 --> 00:32:20,708
I used to walk my dog
every morning around this time…

648
00:32:23,416 --> 00:32:26,708
because the summer asphalt burns
a dog's paws like a cigarette.

649
00:32:29,541 --> 00:32:31,625
When he got older and his legs were weak,

650
00:32:32,375 --> 00:32:35,958
I'd put him in a cart
or just take him for shorter walks.

651
00:32:38,208 --> 00:32:39,291
Omochi.

652
00:32:41,583 --> 00:32:44,375
He looked so happy
when he got to sniff the breeze.

653
00:32:45,875 --> 00:32:47,125
That face…

654
00:32:48,083 --> 00:32:49,916
As I walked,
I'd wonder how many more times

655
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,541
I'd get to see that face.

656
00:32:56,333 --> 00:32:57,458
When I was a kid,

657
00:32:58,291 --> 00:33:00,375
I used to get beatings and give beatings.

658
00:33:01,291 --> 00:33:04,166
I went through so much shit
that my heart turned to stone.

659
00:33:07,791 --> 00:33:08,708
[groans softly]

660
00:33:09,291 --> 00:33:11,750
Dogs can understand
what's going on in your heart.

661
00:33:12,708 --> 00:33:15,833
He'd come to comfort me and lick my face.

662
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:21,208
When I rubbed my nose in Omochi's fur
and took a deep breath,

663
00:33:21,875 --> 00:33:25,291
I smelled something I couldn't describe,
a smell that always calmed me down.

664
00:33:28,416 --> 00:33:29,833
After my mom died,

665
00:33:30,875 --> 00:33:33,708
Omochi was the only one
I could open my heart up to.

666
00:33:35,416 --> 00:33:37,250
Omochi died of old age, right?

667
00:33:42,958 --> 00:33:45,041
I killed him on Kyogoku's orders.

668
00:33:45,125 --> 00:33:46,041
[dramatic sting]

669
00:33:46,833 --> 00:33:50,750
It's Kyogoku I should have killed
and let myself die back then.

670
00:33:50,833 --> 00:33:52,833
[tense music playing]

671
00:33:54,125 --> 00:33:55,625
But now's not the time.

672
00:33:57,708 --> 00:33:59,875
There are a few things I have left to do.

673
00:34:01,458 --> 00:34:06,625
The only way poor people can afford
to get off is with free videos,

674
00:34:06,708 --> 00:34:10,166
so no wonder sex crimes never go away.

675
00:34:10,750 --> 00:34:11,625
Huh?

676
00:34:12,625 --> 00:34:14,291
DIAMOND IN THE ROUGH, SHIZUKU PIEN

677
00:34:15,416 --> 00:34:16,875
[Shizuku] <i>Nice to meet you.</i>

678
00:34:17,291 --> 00:34:19,541
SHIZUKU PIEN

679
00:34:19,625 --> 00:34:22,333
- [Tonohata] What the hell?
<i>- I'm Shizuku Pien.</i>

680
00:34:22,416 --> 00:34:24,083
That's Shizuku, isn't it?

681
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:32,000
Thank you so much for taking time
out of your busy schedule.

682
00:34:32,083 --> 00:34:35,916
I was impressed by your online articles
and videos, Attorney Kameoka.

683
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:37,916
Right, thank you very much.

684
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:39,541
[Tonohata] Shizuku is only 19.

685
00:34:40,041 --> 00:34:41,708
Used to be that was a minor.

686
00:34:41,791 --> 00:34:47,166
Even though the legal age of adulthood
may be 18 now, she still has no idea!

687
00:34:47,250 --> 00:34:49,375
She's operating with the mind of a child.

688
00:34:50,541 --> 00:34:51,958
It's unforgivable.

689
00:34:52,041 --> 00:34:54,500
Those greedy studio heads
tricked my daughter,

690
00:34:54,583 --> 00:34:55,916
who is practically a child,

691
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:59,125
and made her a public spectacle
for the rest of her life!

692
00:34:59,208 --> 00:35:02,625
Attorney, can you help us
get as much compensation as possible?

693
00:35:03,708 --> 00:35:06,250
Ms. Kasagi, may I ask you something?

694
00:35:06,333 --> 00:35:07,333
Sure.

695
00:35:07,416 --> 00:35:08,833
[music fades]

696
00:35:08,916 --> 00:35:12,583
Shizuku's appearance contract
has your signature on it.

697
00:35:12,666 --> 00:35:13,583
As her parent,

698
00:35:13,666 --> 00:35:16,166
shouldn't you have put more thought
into protecting your daughter?

699
00:35:16,250 --> 00:35:19,041
Why are you…
trying to put the blame on me?

700
00:35:19,125 --> 00:35:20,041
How could I have known?

701
00:35:20,125 --> 00:35:23,583
You could have known
since you signed the contract

702
00:35:23,666 --> 00:35:25,250
as a witness to an agreement.

703
00:35:25,333 --> 00:35:26,708
I'm telling you.

704
00:35:26,791 --> 00:35:29,583
She told me it was a form
for her job at the store.

705
00:35:29,666 --> 00:35:31,708
How was I supposed to know
it was that kind of work?

706
00:35:31,791 --> 00:35:34,000
Even so,
her mother having signed the contract

707
00:35:34,083 --> 00:35:36,416
would be unfavorable to any case we bring.

708
00:35:36,500 --> 00:35:38,000
According to the terms of the contract,

709
00:35:38,083 --> 00:35:40,125
no fault whatsoever
can be attributed to the studio.

710
00:35:40,208 --> 00:35:43,500
What the hell, Kinuko?!
You signed it without asking?!

711
00:35:44,541 --> 00:35:46,541
Attorney,
please take them for all you can.

712
00:35:46,625 --> 00:35:48,250
You must hate them too, right?

713
00:35:48,333 --> 00:35:50,458
It's irrelevant whether
I hate them or not.

714
00:35:50,541 --> 00:35:52,583
Let's not forget
that we're the victims here.

715
00:35:52,666 --> 00:35:54,291
Surely you can do something.

716
00:35:56,625 --> 00:35:57,625
I understand.

717
00:35:58,416 --> 00:36:00,833
The contract doesn't mention
the sex industry,

718
00:36:00,916 --> 00:36:03,500
and it doesn't even specify
the nature of the work involved.

719
00:36:04,166 --> 00:36:07,500
The employers set an unreasonable penalty
for breach of contract

720
00:36:07,583 --> 00:36:09,750
and even got her mother
to sign as a witness.

721
00:36:09,833 --> 00:36:12,708
All this is evidence
of a contract intended to deceive.

722
00:36:12,791 --> 00:36:16,083
When we're in court,
we need to pursue the question of whether

723
00:36:16,583 --> 00:36:20,208
the studio adequately explained to Shizuku
the fact that she would be filmed

724
00:36:20,291 --> 00:36:22,208
during a sexual performance

725
00:36:22,291 --> 00:36:26,291
and the question of whether they got
her informed consent after that.

726
00:36:26,375 --> 00:36:28,541
How much could we get in compensation?

727
00:36:29,583 --> 00:36:32,125
Was there a figure you had in mind,
Mr. Tonohata?

728
00:36:32,208 --> 00:36:35,500
I say we ought to be aiming
for 30 million at least. Right, Attorney?

729
00:36:35,583 --> 00:36:38,875
I think the best we can do is five.
We might end up with even less.

730
00:36:38,958 --> 00:36:41,333
So, five million tops, huh?

731
00:36:41,416 --> 00:36:45,250
So, that means we're talking maybe two
or three million if they lowball us.

732
00:36:46,083 --> 00:36:47,083
Pretty good.

733
00:36:47,166 --> 00:36:49,750
What do you mean?
That's nowhere near enough for us.

734
00:36:49,833 --> 00:36:52,333
Well, Attorney, please look after this.

735
00:36:52,416 --> 00:36:56,791
Well, then, we'll file a claim against
